Deploy a Virtual Machine (VM) on Google Cloud – Simple Steps (Exam Answer)

Open GCP Console

Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
 and log in with your Google account.

Open Compute Engine

From the left side menu → click Compute Engine → click VM Instances.

Create a New Instance

Click on Create Instance button.

Select Machine Type and OS

Choose Machine type: e2-micro (small free-tier VM).

Under Boot Disk, select Ubuntu operating system with default disk size.

Use Default Settings

Keep all other settings (network, firewall, disk) as default.

Create the VM

Click Create.

After a few seconds the VM status becomes Running.

Open the VM Using SSH

Click the SSH button next to the VM name.

A browser terminal will open and you can use Linux commands inside the VM.

Take Screenshots

Take screenshot of the VM Instances Dashboard.

Take screenshot of the SSH Terminal showing the Ubuntu prompt.



